text: Ross Stephenson Moore (1809 – 5 October 1855) was an Irish Conservative Party politician. Moore was elected Conservative Member of Parliament (MP) for Armagh City at the 1852 general election but died before sitting for a full term in 1855. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1809 births Category:1855 deaths Category:Irish Conservative Party MPs Category:Members of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for County Armagh constituencies (1801–1922) Category:UK MPs 1847–1852
